<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<!--
  vmenu.entitlements — App Sandbox rationale

  The App Sandbox is intentionally disabled because vmenu requires
  capabilities that are incompatible with the sandbox:

  1. Process spawning (NSTask / Process):
     vmenu executes /bin/launchctl to bootstrap, bootout, kickstart,
     and inspect the Vault LaunchAgent service.  It also runs
     /usr/bin/which to locate the vault binary.  The App Sandbox does
     not permit process spawning via posix_spawn / NSTask; there is
     no entitlement to allow it.

  2. File system access outside the sandbox container:
     vmenu reads and writes ~/Library/LaunchAgents/com.hashicorp.vault.plist
     to manage the Vault LaunchAgent lifecycle.  It also reads CA
     certificate files at user-specified paths and Vault log files.

  3. Outbound network connections:
     vmenu polls the local Vault server's /v1/sys/seal-status endpoint
     over HTTPS (typically https://127.0.0.1:8200).

  To enable sandboxing, the architecture would need to change to use
  a privileged XPC helper (SMAppService / SMJobBless) for launchctl
  operations and file writes outside the container, while keeping the
  menu-bar UI in a sandboxed main app.  This is tracked as a future
  improvement.

  Defense-in-depth mitigations currently in place:
  - Hardened Runtime is enabled (see code-signing flags).
  - Allow-unsigned-executable-memory is explicitly disabled.
  - Library validation is not disabled (only signed libraries load).
  - All network requests use ephemeral URLSession (no credential caching).
  - CA certificate paths are validated against symlink and traversal attacks.
  - The app has no document types, URL schemes, or IPC surface.
-->
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <key>com.apple.security.app-sandbox</key>
    <false/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <false/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <false/>
</dict>
</plist>
